<p>
	Thyme essential oil is a strong antiseptic oil with stimulating properties. Used in an oil burner, a few drops in the bath or blended as a massage oil or cream thyme oil can help with concentration, memory and focus, it has warming qualities that are great for conditions such as rheumatism, sciatica, arthritis and gout.</p>
<p>
	It is also known to fortify the lungs which helps with colds, coughs, asthma, laryngitis, sinusitis, catarrh and whooping cough plus sore throats and tonsillitis.</p>
<p>
	The therapeutic properties of thyme oil include antirheumatic, antiseptic, antispasmodic, bactericidal, cardiac, carminative, diuretic, expectorant, hypertensive, insecticide, stimulant, tonic and vermifuge.</p>
<p>
